==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sandal
<hw>San"dal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>sandale</ets>, L.
<ets>sandalium</ets>, Gr. <?/, dim. of <?/, probably from Per.
<ets>sandal</ets>.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A kind of shoe consisting of
a sole strapped to the foot; a protection for the foot, covering its
lower surface, but not its upper.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A kind of
slipper.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>An overshoe with parallel openings
across the instep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sandaled</ent>⟦br⟧
